==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Semblant
<hw>Sem"blant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>semblant</ets>, p. pr.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Like;
resembling.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Prior.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Seeming, rather than real; apparent.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Carlyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semblant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Semblant
<hw>Sem"blant</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Show;
appearance; figure; semblance.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His flatterers made <qex>semblant</qex> of weeping.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The face.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Wyclif
(Luke xxiv. 5).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semblative</ent>⟦br⟧
